$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):EXP_PROC
$DATUM [(Hydroxy)(tosyloxy)iodo]thiophene (11c). To a solution of compound 10b
(500 mg, 1.52 mmol) was added to solution of p-toluenesulfonic acid
monohydrate (290 mg, 1.52 mmol) in acetonitrile (10 mL) at room
temperature under nitrogen atmosphere. The mixture was stirred for 1 h at
room temperature. After the addition of diethyl ether and EtOAc (v/v =
2:1, 30 mL), the solid was filtered and dried in a short time under
nitrogen atmosphere to give the product 11c (95%). Because this product
(11c) was unstable under air atmosphere and at room temperature, it was
used immediately after isolation to prepare the next compound, 12c:
[(Hydroxy)(tosyloxy)iodo]thiophene (11c), yield (95%) 1H NMR (400 MHz,
CD3- OD) δ 2.36 (s, 3H), 4.88 (s, 3H), 7.22 (d, J = 8.0 Hz, 2H),
7.35-7.37 (m, 1H), 7.68 (d, J = 8.4 Hz, 2H), 8.09-8.10 (m, 1H), 8.24-8.25
(m, 1H); 13C NMR (100 MHz, CD3OD) δ 21.30, 126.95, 129.83, 131.19,
141.39, 141.76, 143.29, 143.38, 145.23.
$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):REFERENCE(1):TITLE
$DATUM Strategies for the Labeling of Halogen-Substituted Peroxisome
Proliferator-Activated Receptor γ Ligands: Potential Positron Emission
Tomography and Single Photon Emission Computed Tomography Imaging Agents
$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):REFERENCE(1):AUTHOR
$DATUM Lee, Byung Chul; Lee, Kyo Chul; Lee, Hsiaoju; Mach, Robert H.;

$DATUM Hydrogen (±)-α,α'-di-tert-butylsuccinate, tetramethylammonium salt.
(±)-α,α'-Di-tert-butylsuccinic acid (80.7 mg, 0.35 mmol) was dissolved in
126 µL of a 25% w/w Me4NOH(aq) solution (0.35 mmol). The solution was
concentrated under vacuum to give a yellow oil. The oil was dissolved in
ethanol and the solvent was allowed to evaporate to give a solid residue.
This residue was recrystallized successively from methylene chloride and
THF to give needle-like crystals. Yield 100 mg (0.33 mmol), 94%. mp 92-95
ºC. 1H NMR (400 MHz, CDCl3): δ 1.01 (s, 18 H), 2.45 (s, 2 H), 3.35 (s, 12
H). 1H NMR (400 MHz, DMSO-d 6): δ 0.93 (s, 18 H), 2.18 (s, 2 H), 3.09 (s,
12 H), 19.55 (s, 1 H).
$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):REFERENCE(1):TITLE

(±)-α,α'-Di-tert-butylsuccinate

$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):EXP_PROC
$DATUM General/Typical Procedure: (Bu4N)2(me-ida). N-Methyliminodiacetic acid
(2.100 g, 14.27 mmol) was dissolved in water (10.0 ml) and to this
solution was added dropwise a 40% w/w aqueous solution of (n-Bu4N)OH
(18.52 g, 28.55 mmol) via an addition funnel over ~20 minutes. The
majority of the water was removed from the resulting clear colorless
solution was by rotary evaporation to yield a viscous liquid. Further
drying in vacuo at room temperature for 36 hours gave a white powder.
Recrystallization from hot CH3CN under Ar gave an anhydrous, white
crystalline material after standing at 12 hours at -36 °C (yield 8.273 g,
92%). This solid was dried in vacuo at room temperature and was used
without further purification. a(n-Et4N)2(tbu-ida), yield 93.8% Calculated
for C25H53N3O4 ; Elemental Analysis C: Calc: 64.39 Found: 63.82 ; H 11.93
12.18 ; N 9.39 9.24 ; 1H NMR (δ, ppm) 1.05 (s, 9H); 1.21 (t, 24H); 2.95
(s, 4H); 3.20 (q, 16H)

$DATUM General/Typical Procedure: General Procedure for Cyanoethyl Ester
Cleavage. To a solution of phosphosugars 5 (1.0 equiv) in a mixture of
CH2Cl2/H2O (2:1, 9 mL/mmol of 5) was added at room temperature
tetrabutylammonium hydroxide (1 M in water, 1.2 equiv). The reaction
mixture was stirred 2 h at room temperature before it was diluted with
CH2Cl2 and washed with saturated aqueous NaHCO3. The organic layer was
washed with brine, dried (MgSO4), and concentrated under reduced
pressure. The obtained ammonium salt was used for the next step without
purification. Tetrabutylammonium benzyl
(1,2:5,6-di-isopropylidene-α-D-glucofuranos-3-yl) phosphate (6a).
Tetrabutylammonium benzyl (methyl
2,3,6-tri-O-acetyl-α-D-glucopyranosid-4-yl) phosphate (6b). Colourless
oil, 94%. [α]25 D + 50.2 (c, 1.0, CHCl3). 1H NMR (300 MHz, CDCl3) δ: 0.90
(t, J = 7.2 Hz, 12H), 1.26-1.40 (m, 8H), 1.47-1.60 (m, 8H), 1.70 (s, 3H),
1.97 (s, 6H), 3.16-3.26 (m, 8H), 3.32 (s, 3H), 3.86-3.95 (m, 1H), 4.21
(dd, J = 8.2 Hz, J = 11.8 Hz, 1H), 4.29-4.36 (m, 1H), 4.61 (d, J = 11.8
Hz, 1H), 4.69-4.84 (m, 3H), 4.89-4.99 (m, 1H), 5.42 (t, J = 9.7 Hz, 1H),
7.07-7.21 (m, 3H), 7.27-7.35 (m, 2H); 13C NMR (75 MHz, CDCl3) δ: 13.7,
19.7, 20.8, 20.9, 21.0, 24.0, 54.8, 58.7, 64.6, 66.7, 69.0, 71.0, 71.7,
77.3, 96.4, 126.6, 127.1, 127.8, 140.1, 170.3, 170.3, 170.6, 170.9;31P
NMR (121 MHz, CDCl3) δ: - 0.72. ESIHRMS Calcd for C20H26O12P [M -
n-Bu4N+]-: 489.1162, found 489.1160.

$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):EXP_PROC
$DATUM General/Typical Procedure: Tetra-n-butylammonium
4-Hydroxymethylphenyltrifluoroborate (1a). 4-Hydroxymethylphenylboronic
acid (1.52 g, 10.0 mmol) was slurried in H2O (15 mL) at 0 °C in an
ice/water bath. KHF2 (1.56 g, 20.0 mmol) was added all at once as a
solid. The mixture was stirred for 2 h at 0 °C at which point H2O (6 mL)
was used to rinse the neck and sides of the flask. After stirring for an
additional 2 h, CH2Cl2 (15 mL) was added followed by n-Bu4NOH (1.61M,
6.25 mL, 10.1 mmol) via syringe. After stirring for 0.5 h, the biphasic
mixture was transferred to a separatory funnel, rinsing with CH2Cl2 (10
mL). The layers were shaken and separated and the aqueous layer was
further extracted with CH2Cl2 (10 mL, 15 mL). The combined organic layers
were dried (Na2SO4) and concentrated to give an oil which solidified to
yellow crystals (3.70 g, 89% yield): Tetra-n-butylammonium
3-Hydroxymethylphenyltrifluoroborate (1b). This compound was synthesized
from 3-hydroxymethylboronic acid according to the procedure used for 1a
to give a yellow oil which solidified upon standing (785 mg, 94% yield):
mp 55-57 °C; 1H NMR (500 MHz, CDCl3) δ 7.60 (s, 1H), 7.56 (d, J = 7.2 Hz,
1H), 7.21 (t, J = 7.4 Hz, 1H), 7.15 (d, J = 7.5 Hz, 1H), 4.62 (s, 2H),
3.11-3.08 (m, 8H), 1.56-1.50 (m, 8H), 1.37 (sextet, J = 7.3 Hz, 8H), 0.97
(t, J = 7.3 Hz, 12H); 13C NMR (125 MHz, CDCl3) δ 138.9, 131.3, 130.9,
127.0, 124.7, 66.0, 58.3, 23.7, 19.6, 13.7; 11B NMR (128 MHz, CDCl3) δ
2.87 (br s); 19F NMR (471 MHz, CDCl3) δ -142.1 (m); IR (film) 3515, 2963,
2876 cm-1; HRMS calcd. for C7H7BF3O [M-(NBu4)]- 175.0542, found 175.0551.
$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):REFERENCE(1):TITLE

$DATUM Synthesis of [NBu n 4][Re2(CO)8(μ-Ph2GeOGePh2)(μ-H)]- ([NBu n 4]•5). A
80.0 μL sample of a 1.0 M solution of [NBu n 4]- [OH] in methanol (0.081
mmol) was added to a solution of 4 (86 mg, 0.080 mmol) in 5 mL of hexane
at room temperature, upon which a white precipitate formed. After 30 min,
the precipitate was collected by filtration, washed with hexane, and
recrystallized from methanol to give 90.3 mg (94% yield) of [NBu n 4]•5.
Spectral data for [NBu n 4]•5: IR ν CO (cm-1 in CH2Cl2): 2078 (m), 2053
(w), 1985 (s), 1963 (sh), 1920 (m). 1H NMR (CD2Cl2 in ppm): δ 7.1- 7.7
(m, 20 H, Ph), 2.63 (t, 8 H, CH2), 1.22 (m, 16 H, CH2), 0.91 (t, 12 H,
CH3), -15.2 (s, 1 H, μ-H). MS (negative ion electrospray) for 5: m/e =
1067 (M-) with an isotope distribution pattern for Re2Ge2.

$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):EXP_PROC
$DATUM 1,1-Dimethylethyl (3S)-Amino-5-(trimethylsilyl)-4-pentynoate
4-Methylphenylsulfonate Salt (7). A solution of 6 (123.3 g, 0.374 mol) in
dry THF (350 mL) was prepared. p-Toluenesulfonic acid monohydrate (71.2
g, 0.374 mol) was charged to a 4 L jacketed reaction vessel under
nitrogen. An overhead stirrer with a 10 cm Teflon stir blade was
attached. A thermocouple thermometer was put in place. The reactor jacket
was cooled to 0 °C. The solution of 6 was added via an addition funnel
over 5 min with stirring at 250 rpm. The reaction temperature rose to 10
°C. The addition funnel was rinsed with THF (300 mL). After stirring for
15 min the mixture became homogeneous. The stirring rate was increased to
350 rpm. Heptane (1360 mL) was added over 5 min. The product crystallized
and the agitation was increased to 540 rpm. The solvent was distilled
from the reactor under vacuum under the following conditions. An oil pump
connected to a vacuum regulator was used to adjust the vacuum to 45 mmHg.
The jacket temperature was set to 20 °C and a dry ice/2- propanol
condenser with a 2 L receiving flask was used to collect the distillate.
The distillate collected was 900 mL. The reactor was placed under a
nitrogen atmosphere and additional heptane (900 mL) was added. The slurry
was cooled to 2 °C. The solids were collected on a 10 cm coarse glass
fritted filter with a vacuum. The reaction vessel was rinsed by adding
heptane (500 mL) and THF (50 mL) with stirring. The reaction mixture was
cooled to 10 °C and added to the filter. The cake was washed with heptane
(3 × 300 mL) and dried by using a combination of vacuum and nitrogen flow
for 4.5 h to produce 7 (145.9 g, 94%); mp 142 °C; 1H NMR (CDCl3, 400 MHz)
δ8.32 (br, s, 3H), 7.79 (d, J = 8.0 Hz, 2H), 7.15 (d, J = 8.0 Hz, 2H),
4.40 (dd, J = 8.0 and 6.0 Hz, 1H), 2.89 (dd, J = 17.0 and 8.0 Hz, 1H),
2.76 (dd, J = 17.0 and 5.0 Hz, 1H), 2.36 (s, 3H), 1.41 (s, 9H), 0.10 (s,
9H); 13C NMR (CDCl3, 125 MHz) δ168.6, 141.6, 140.2, 128.8 (2C), 126.1
(2C), 98.5, 92.7, 82.0, 40.6, 38.6, 27.9 (3C), 21.3, -0.5 (3C). Anal.
Calcd for C19 H31NO5SSi: C, 55.17; H, 7.55; N, 3.39. Found: C, 55.27; H,
7.27; N, 3.34.

$DTYPE RXN:VAR(1):EXP_PROC
$DATUM General/Typical Procedure: Example 111 a - Preparation of Compound 2B
(HCl salt of 3-amino-2-hydroxy-benzamide (compound (IV(i))). To a
suspension of 10 g (34.6 mmol) of (IV) in a mixture of 21 ml of methyl
t-butylether and 49 ml of ethanol was added 13.7 ml of KOEt (24%) in
ethanol, followed by addition of 0.8 g of 5% Pd/C (50% wet). The mixture
was then agitated under 120-150 psi hydrogen pressure for about 6 hours.
Upon completion of the reaction, the batch was filtered through a Celite
pad and the cake was washed with 80 ml of solvent mixture of methyl
t-butylether and ethanol (1:1). The filtrate was treated with 3.7 ml of
concentrated HCl solution. The batch was then concentrated under reduced
pressure to about 50 ml. Isopropanol (100 ml) was added and the resulting
solution was concentrated under vacuum to about 40 ml. Methyl
t-butylether (50 ml) was added, followed by a slow addition of 110 ml of
heptane. Finally, the mixture was cooled to 0°C. The solids were
collected by filtration and the cake was washed with 20 ml solvent
mixture of 1:1 methyl t-butylether/EtOH. The cake was dried at 60°C for
10 hours in a vacuum oven, to give 7.24 g (96%) off-white solids of the
compound of Formula 2B. Example 111c - Preparation of
3-amino-2-hydroxy-benzamide p-Tolysulfonate Salt (2B3) Following the
procedure described for preparing the HCl salt (2B) in Preparative
Example 1, the compound of Formula 2B3 was prepared by placing 10 g of
compound (IV) was hydrogenated under the same condition and the filtrate
was treated with 7.9 g (41.1 mmol) p-toluenesulfonic acid monohydrate.
The resulting mixture was concentrated as above and the mixture after
heptane addition was stirred over night at room temperature, to give 11.4
g (94%) off-white solids. 3-amino-2-hydroxy-benzamide p-Tolysulfonate 1H
NMR(DMSO-D6): 7.49 (d, 2H), 7.29 (d, 1H), 7.15 (m, 3H), 6.93 (dd, 1H),
2.90 (s, 6H), 2.31 (s, 3H).

$DATUM General/Typical Procedure: Dimethyl
2-({tert-Butyl[(4-methylphenyl)sulfonyl]amino}carbonyl)-3-hydroxysuccinate
(3a); Typical Procedure To a magnetically stirred solution of dimethyl
acetylenedicarboxylate (2a; 0.14 g, 1 mmol) and 4-methylbenzenesulfonic
acid monohydrate (0.19 g, 1 mmol) in anhyd CH2Cl2 (5 mL) was added
dropwise a solution of tert-butyl isocyanide (1a; 0.083 g, 1 mmol) in
anhyd CH2Cl2 (3 mL) at r.t. over 10 min. The mixture was then allowed to
stir for 48 h. The solvent was removed under reduced pressure, and the
residue was purified by silica gel (Merck 230-240 mesh) column
chromatography using hexane-EtOAc mixture as eluent. Diethyl
2-({Cyclohexyl[(4-methylphenyl)sulfonyl]amino}carbonyl)-3-hydroxysuccinate
(3e), colorless crystals, yield 0.44 g (94%). mp 105-107 °C. IR (KBr):
3395 (OH), 1728 (C=O of CO2Et), 1665 (C=O of CON), 1600 and 1442 (Ar),
1353 and 1180 (SO2), 1240 and 1200 cm-1 (C-O of ester). 1H NMR (500 MHz,
CDCl3): δ = 1.16-1.95 (10 H, m, 5 CH2 of cyclohexyl), 1.17 (3 H, t, J =
7.1 Hz, OCH2CH3), 1.35 (3 H, t, J = 7.1 Hz, OCH2CH3), 2.41 (3 H, s, CH3),
3.57 (1 H, m, CHN of cyclohexyl), 4.11 (1 H, d, J = 8.1 Hz, CH),
4.25-4.35 (4 H, m, 2 OCH2CH3), 4.50 (1 H, s, OH), 4.61 (1 H, d, J = 8.1
Hz, CHO), 7.28 (2 H, d, J = 8.1 Hz, 2 CH of Ar), 7.79 (2 H, d, J = 8.1
Hz, 2 CH of Ar). 13C NMR (125.7 MHz, CDCl3): δ = 13.89 (OCH2CH3), 14.08
(OCH2CH3), 21.60 (CH3 of Ar), 24.34, 24.51, 25.62, 32.50, 32.63 (5 CH2 of
cyclohexyl), 51.63 (CH), 53.78 (OCH2CH3), 60.90 (CHN), 62.49 (OCH2CH3),
63.46 (CHOH), 129.08 (2 CH of Ar), 129.55 (2 CH of Ar), 131.15
(Cipso-SO2), 144.06 (Cipso-CH3), 153.17 (CON), 166.20 (CO2Et), 169.18
(CO2Et). MS: m/z (%) = 466 (2), 311 (3), 310 (19), 229 (6), 156 (17), 91
(80), 55 (100), 41 (61). Anal. Calcd for C22H31NO8S (469.54): C, 56.28;
H, 6.65; N, 2.98. Found: C, 56.34; H, 6.75; N, 3.00.
